Cleanning Dataset¶

Writing function to handle missing values in new_deaths, new_tests, new_cases,people_vaccinated, people_fully_vaccinated colums

In [10]:
def fill_cols(col):
    cols=[0]
    for i in range(len(col)):
        if col.values[i]==' ':
            cols.append(cols[-1])  
        else:
            cols.append(col.values[i])  
    return cols

Writing function to handle missing values in total_cases and total_deaths columns

In [11]:
def fill_cols2(col1,col2):
    new_col=[0]
    for i in range(len(col1)):
        if col1.values[i]==' ':
            new_col.append(col2.values[i]+new_col[-1])  
        else:
            new_col.append(col1.values[i])  
    return new_col

Cleanning the dataset based on location

In [12]:
def clean_dataset(dataset):
    data=dataset[:0]
    for countr in dataset['location'].unique():
        dat=dataset[dataset['location']==countr].copy()
        dat['new_deaths']=dat['new_deaths'].fillna(value=0)
        dat['new_tests']=dat['new_tests'].fillna(value=0)
        dat['new_cases']=dat['new_cases'].fillna(value=0)

        dat['people_vaccinated']=dat['people_vaccinated'].fillna(value=' ')
        dat['people_vaccinated']=fill_cols(dat['people_vaccinated'])[1:]

        dat['people_fully_vaccinated']=dat['people_fully_vaccinated'].fillna(value=' ')
        dat['people_fully_vaccinated']=fill_cols(dat['people_fully_vaccinated'])[1:]

        dat['total_cases']=dat['total_cases'].fillna(value=' ')
        dat['total_deaths']=dat['total_deaths'].fillna(value=' ')

        dat['total_cases']=fill_cols2(dat['total_cases'],dat['new_cases'])[1:]
        dat['total_deaths']=fill_cols2(dat['total_deaths'],dat['new_deaths'])[1:]
        data=pd.concat([data,dat])
         
    return data

Preparing dataset for LSTM Model¶

In [28]:
#preparing independent and dependent features
def prepare_data(timeseries_data,n_features):
    X,Y = [],[]
    for i in range(len(timeseries_data)):
        end_ix = i+n_features
        #check if we are beyond the sequence
        if end_ix>len(timeseries_data)-1:
            break
        #gather input and output parts of the pattern
        seq_x,seq_y=timeseries_data[i:end_ix],timeseries_data[end_ix]
        X.append(seq_x)
        Y.append(seq_y)
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

for clf, clf_name in zip(clfs.values(), clfs.keys()):
    clf.fit(X_train,y_train)
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_train)
    y_score = clf.score(X_train,y_train)

                   )

    models_report = models_report.append(t, ignore_index = True)

def plot_feature_importances_cancer(model):
    plt.title("Features importances")
    n_features = X_train.shape[1]
    plt.barh(np.arange(n_features), model.feature_importances_, align='center')
    plt.yticks(np.arange(n_features),X_train.columns)
    plt.xlabel("Feature importance")
    plt.ylabel("Features")
    plt.ylim(-1, n_features)
